# Remove the example slice

This site was generated with `--starter`, which added one small, runnable example — a
**model → repository → service → controller (on the Corex response envelope) → block →
option page → test** — so you can see how a Corex client site is wired end to end. Once
you've read it, delete it and build your own.

## 1. Delete these files

- `src/Models/Example.php`
- `src/Repositories/ExampleRepository.php`
- `src/Services/ExampleService.php`
- `src/Controllers/ExampleController.php`
- `src/Blocks/ExampleRenderer.php`
- `src/Blocks/example/` (block.json, index.js, style.scss)
- `src/Options/ExampleOptions.php`
- `tests/ExampleTest.php`
- `REMOVE-EXAMPLE.md` (this file)

## 2. Unwire it

In `src/{{ namespace }}ServiceProvider.php`, remove the lines in `register()`/`boot()` that
construct and register the Example controller, options page, and block. Then run
`npm run build` in the `{{ theme_slug }}` theme to drop the example block's compiled assets.

## 3. Build your own

Write your code in **this plugin** (`{{ namespace }}\…`) and the **`{{ theme_slug }}` theme** —
never in the Corex framework folders. Generate new pieces with `wp corex make:*`.
